fields.text:
@priya re: your context from slack 8cadb42f0d894829 on the NPCI sync – yeah, we've hit a pretty solid roadblock with the UPI LITE X integration. 

The KYC automation is failing consistently, but only for high-risk customer segments. Our fraud-engine is timing out calling their sandbox whenever we test with profiles like unique_id 367426. No useful error codes back from their side, just a generic timeout. 😕

This is blocking the entire offline payment flow validation for work ID 04da84ad-10cc-4e23-b547-2eb09883fb5a. I've updated JIRA PAY-3240 with the Grafana traces and have already looped in our NPCI contact with the payloads. If we don't get a proper response from them by EOD, we should probably escalate.

@Priya Sharma circling back on the PCI audit finding you flagged in slack 23fb86a588524e5f. Just had a productive call with the NPCI team about it.

They've acknowledged the gap (finding ID 281090) and are proposing a patch on their end for the UPI LITE X offline payment flow. It's related to the data handling in the NFC handshake, and their initial take is that it won't require any changes to our core payment-gateway logic. So, no expected impact on our TPS or latency. 🤞

I've updated JIRA PAY-5378 with my call notes. We need our Hyper SDK team to validate their proposed fix ASAP. I'm trying to set up a 20-min tech sync with them before EOD. Who's the best person from our side to join? Need to move fast on this for work ID 04da84ad-10cc-4e23-b547-2eb09883fb5a.

@priya yup, seeing the same drop in transaction throughput on my dashboard 📉. Just got off a quick call with our NPCI contact for the UPI LITE X integration. 

It seems they've put a temporary, much lower rate limit on their endpoints post their infra issue yesterday – without giving us a heads-up 😕. This is directly impacting work ID 04da84ad-10cc-4e23-b547-2eb09883fb5a. 

I've escalated this and stressed that our throughput is well within the contracted limits. I've also logged all the details under incident ID 629990 and updated JIRA PAY-9219. Pushing them for an ETA on getting the limits restored. Will ping here the moment I have an update.

@priya_kapoor circling back on your multi-currency settlement question from 3c7ff231c03044c3. Just got off a call with the NPCI team for the UPI LITE X integration (work ID 04da84ad-10cc-4e23-b547-2eb09883fb5a).

Looks like their settlement engine isn't built to handle multi-currency batching directly for these offline payments. 😕 They're proposing we receive the settlement files in INR and then run the forex conversion through our own Euler flow. It definitely adds a reconciliation step we need to account for.

I've updated JIRA PAY-9906 with their notes and the proposed flow (ref ID 158420). Can we sync tomorrow to discuss feasibility on our end? Lmk.

@PriyaSharma just saw the audit report. That PCI finding on the UPI LITE X offline payment flow is a blocker 🚨. Have logged it as JIRA PAY-1980 and escalated internally.

This is a P0 for the entire NPCI integration (work ID 04da84ad-10cc-4e23-b547-2eb09883fb5a). I can't give NPCI the green light for UAT with this open. The finding is ID #742775 from the report, btw.

@dev-team what's the plan for remediation in the Hyper SDK? We need to give NPCI a concrete timeline asap. Let's sync up before EOD.

@Priya re: the KYC automation failures from slack a542ea3c48014697 – I’ve been digging into the logs. It looks like our fraud-engine is timing out when scoring the high-risk customer profiles. Grafana is showing a direct correlation between these timeouts and the KYC failure rate spiking 📉.

Ran a BigQuery query and it's definitely isolated to that segment. The Hyper SDK is just passing the timeout error from upstream, so I don’t think the issue is on the client-side. I've logged the specifics in JIRA PAY-8054 for this UPI LITE X project (work ID 04da84ad-10cc-4e23-b547-2eb09883fb5a).

Probably need to either optimize the scoring rules or just increase the service timeout. We should get the fraud team's input before we update NPCI. 🤔

@priya.sharma Re your point on the multi-currency settlement from slack a105d813edf747c0, just got off a call with the NPCI team about the UPI LITE X integration.

They've pushed back on our proposed real-time FX model. 😕 Seems their current infrastructure for unique ID 904888 can't support it and they're insisting we align with their standard EOD batch process for currency conversion. This definitely complicates things for the payment-gateway's reconciliation logic.

I've updated JIRA PAY-7372 with their formal feedback. We probably need to rethink our approach for work ID 04da84ad-10cc-4e23-b547-2eb09883fb5a. Maybe we can build a temporary buffer on our side? Lmk what you think.

@Priya Sharma yep, that PCI finding is a big one. 🚨 I just got off a call with the NPCI team about this specific item (#243922) from the audit.

They're aligned on the urgency but need our remediation plan EOD. The issue seems to be how our Hyper SDK is storing transaction hashes for offline payments before they hit the payment-gateway. I've updated JIRA PAY-4208 with their technical contact and notes.

This is a critical path dependency for the overall UPI LITE X project (work ID 04da84ad-10cc-4e23-b547-2eb09883fb5a). We'll need a patch plan from engineering ASAP. Who's the best person to scope that out?
